## §1 — Permission Grant (two tiers)

### §1.1 Free Tier — Personal / Research / Education / Small Organization

Permission is hereby granted, **free of charge**, to any person or organization
qualifying as a Free-Tier Licensee, to use, copy, modify, merge, publish,
distribute, sublicense, and create derivative works of the Software, subject
to the Strict Conditions in §3 and the inclusion requirement in §4.

A **Free-Tier Licensee** is any of the following:

  - **a)** A natural person using the Software for personal projects, learning,
    research, art, or non-commercial experimentation.
  - **b)** An accredited educational institution (K-12, college, university)
    using the Software for teaching, coursework, or institutional research.
  - **c)** A non-profit research institute, government research lab, museum,
    or science-education center using the Software for non-commercial research,
    exhibition, or public education.
  - **d)** An open-source project that has no commercial product and no
    revenue-generating service deployment of the Software.
  - **e)** A for-profit organization that, in the immediately preceding
    twelve (12) months, had **all** of the following:
    - gross worldwide revenue of less than US $250,000;
    - five (5) or fewer full-time-equivalent employees, contractors, or
      paid affiliates;
    - no paid product, hosted service, or consulting offering that incorporates
      the Software or any derivative of it.

A Free-Tier Licensee may use the Software in any of the above contexts at no
cost, perpetually, subject to §3 and §4.

### §1.2 Commercial Tier — Paid License Required

Any use of the Software outside the Free-Tier qualifications in §1.1 requires
a separate paid **Commercial License** issued in writing by Anton Pictures.
Commercial-Tier uses include but are not limited to:

  - **a)** A for-profit organization with twelve-month gross worldwide revenue
    of US $250,000 or greater, OR with more than five (5) FTE personnel.
  - **b)** Embedding the Software, any part of it, or any derivative work
    into a product, service, or system that is sold, licensed, or hosted
    for paying third-party customers.
  - **c)** Offering the Software (or any substantially-similar derivative) as
    a managed, hosted, or "as-a-service" offering to third parties.
  - **d)** Bundling the Software with paid hardware, training, support,
    consulting, or certification programs sold to third parties.
  - **e)** Use of the SIFTA name, the bee 🐝 mark, the "Stigmergic Fractals"
    mark, the "Teach Alice to Hear" mark, the "Ace" reading-companion mark,
    the "Coleman Beeson" associative brand, or any confusingly-similar
    derivative thereof, in commerce, requires both a Commercial License
    AND a separately-negotiated Trademark License.

Commercial License inquiries: see `Documents/COMMERCIAL_LICENSE_INQUIRIES.md`.

### §1.3 Tier Transition

A Free-Tier Licensee that crosses any of the Commercial-Tier triggers in §1.2
MUST obtain a Commercial License from Anton Pictures within ninety (90)
calendar days of the triggering event. Continued use after the ninety-day
period without a Commercial License terminates all rights granted under
this License.

